   <h1>Speeding ticket in 75 bus........South Caroninian advice</h1>
   <b>Michael Benthin <benthin(-at-)prodigy.net></b><br/>
   <i>2007-04-19 02:22:40+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>(Note, advice replies are requested off list, as I don't want to clog it 
up  with comments on how to beat a ticket)-but posting your experiences 
with the law while in your bus should be ok......)
      AArrgh, on her way to Everybus from Savannah my college junior 
daughter got caught in a speed trap just before getting onto Rt 95 going 
up Rt 17  from Georgia.  In 7 years of driving her bus this never 
happened to her,
for I know she does the speed limit or at most 5 mph above it.......Rt 
17 goes past a wildlife area (55 mph) and I think the Hardeeville
city limit (town is north of 95) starts just before the onramp, as she 
was literally  stopped on the onramp.  The officer (Badge 511, a woman), 
issued her a
ticket for 20 mph over the limit, apparently not liking the "hippi-van"
as most kind cops would give a ticket for 19mph over the limit to avoid 
the full 4 points.  I'm sure Nyssa could argue her odometer is not the 
best and I think is off at 60 mph. She is insured through the family 
policy.  The court date is May 21 at 36 Main Street, Hardeeville, likely 
a municipal jurisdiction within Jasper County.
    Advice I got at Everybus ranged from "Get a lawyer", argue it to a
lesser "equipment failure" citation, but she won't lie that odometer was 
not working, ask for "probationary judgement"
(points knocked off if you get no tickets in say, a yr, but it's 5 years
in SC!), or offer to take a safe driving course to knock off at least 2
points (4 will definitly raise insurance, which can go over $1000 extra) 
- or just pay the $180 fine and admit you did not
see the sign for the speed drop (she had 3 friends with her).
Any experience the collective group has had with traffic court would be
appreciated- please reply privately ( replyto:benthin(-at-)prodigy.net )
unless you want to comment on experiences you had with your bus- I do
recall that in 1974 I got a ticket going down a hill on Rt 81 12 mi over
the limit just so I could crawl over the next hill without dropping to
25 mph!  My argument: "Well, my average speed is under the limit!" did
not fly with the officer.......

  .   .Mike Benthin in NJ             __ |
  .247K mi on original engine  ______/__\|    (63 panel camper sold)
  .   .   .                  /=__==__===_=\         75 bus
  . . . . 78 VW Camper   -T-|E[__][__]|[_]\\       (77 Westy-sold)
  .  .  . all over USA    0 |  _  |  `|__   |}     (77 Westy-parted)
  .   .                     =-(_)-----(_)`--=   (71 Westy rusto in woods)
                                                 (74 Westy-parted)</pre>


